name: Activity
description: To give an NPC or faction a task or objective, use the Activity oracle. For more detail, you can combine this prompt with the [Focus](id:delve/oracles/feature/focus) oracle or [Theme](id:classic/oracles/action_and_theme/theme) oracle.

name: Disposition
description: Use this oracle when you want to define the initial tone of an encounter with an NPC or faction.

name: Primary Form
description: Some results on these tables include two related options separated by a slash (/). Pick the one which best fits the nature of the creature or is the most interesting. You can also make one of the options likely, and [Ask the Oracle](id:classic/moves/fate/ask_the_oracle) (using the pick two procedure) to confirm your choice. Or just take both!

name: Characteristics
description: Roll up to four times for Characteristics and keep up to three of those results.

name: Abilities
description: Roll up to four times for Abilities and keep up to three of those results.

name: Namesake
description: You may also use your preferred name randomizer to generate a Namesake for your site. If you want to add details for the Namesake, use the [Character oracles](id:classic/collections/oracles/character) in *Ironsworn Core*. This may help inspire a deeper understanding of the history of the site.
